{
 "response": "# Perspective Audit \u2014 Data Table With Sortable Columns and Broken ARIA Sort\n\n## Step 1 \u2014 Escalated Perspectives Confirmed\n\nRunning the full JTBD checklist for the perspectives flagged MEDIUM/HIGH by a11y-critic:\n\n| Perspective | Incoming alarm |\n|---|---|\n| 5. Keyboard & Motor Access | MEDIUM |\n| 6. Screen Reader & Semantic Structure | HIGH |\n| 7. Cognitive & Neurodivergent | MEDIUM |\n\n**Not reviewed (LOW / not escalated):** Magnification & Reflow, Environmental Contrast, Vestibular & Motion Sensitivity, Auditory Access.\n\nOne cross-perspective check was run to decide whether Environmental Contrast (1.4.1) should be re-escalated: sort direction is carried by the \u25b2/\u25bc **glyph shape** (not color alone) and the current page by **bold weight + filled background** (not color alone). Both provide non-color cues for sighted users, so 1.4.1 holds and **no re-escalation is warranted**. The defects that follow are almost entirely programmatic (screen-reader-facing), not visual.\n\n---\n\n## Perspective 5 \u2014 Keyboard & Motor Access (MEDIUM)\n\n### JTBD checklist\n\n| Item (WCAG) | Result | Evidence |\n|---|---|---|\n| All interactive elements keyboard-operable (2.1.1) | **PASS (with MINOR, see K-01)** | Sort headers are real `<button>`; pagination items are real `<a>` with `onClick`. All focusable and activatable. |\n| No keyboard trap (2.1.2) | PASS | No focus-capturing JS; native controls only. |\n| Skip link targets main content (2.4.1) | N/A | Page-level SC; this is a component fragment. |\n| Focus order logical (2.4.3) | PASS | DOM order = sort buttons \u2192 rows \u2192 meta \u2192 pagination, matching visual order. |\n| Focus indicator \u22652px, \u22653:1 (2.4.7, 2.4.13) | PASS | `.sort-btn:focus { outline: 3px solid #1565c0 }`; `.page-link:focus { outline: 3px solid #1565c0; outline-offset: 2px }`. 3px, high-contrast blue. |\n| Multi-point gesture alternative (2.5.1) | N/A | No gestures. |\n| Activation on up-event (2.5.2) | PASS | `onClick` fires on click (up-event); pointer can be dragged off to abort. |\n| Label in name (2.5.3) | PASS | Sort button accessible name = visible text (`{col.label}`; icon span is `aria-hidden`). Pagination visible \"1\" = accessible name \"1\". |\n| Drag has click alternative (2.5.7) | N/A | No drag operations. |\n| Target size \u226524\u00d724 + spacing (2.5.8) | PASS | Sort btn `padding:12px 16px` (~38px tall, full column width). Pagination `padding:8px 12px` (~30\u00d732px) with `gap:8px`. |\n| Portrait + landscape (1.3.4) | PASS | Fluid grid, no orientation lock. |\n\n### Findings\n\n**Finding:** Pagination controls are anchors (`<a href=\"#\">`) styled and functioning as buttons (in-page action, filled/bordered \"button\" appearance). Anchors activate on **Enter only** \u2014 pressing **Space**, the conventional activation key for a button, scrolls the viewport instead of changing the page. A keyboard user who reads the control as a button (its appearance) gets no page change and an unexpected scroll.\n**WCAG:** 4.1.2 Name, Role, Value (Level A) \u2014 a link role is exposed where a button is required, producing inconsistent keyboard operation.\n**Perspective:** Keyboard & Motor Access\n**Severity:** MINOR \u2014 the control remains operable via Enter; degraded, not blocked.\n**Route to:** Front-End Dev (secondary: UX Design)\n**Evidence:** `<a href=\"#\" className={`page-link ...`} onClick={(e) => { e.preventDefault(); setPage(i); }}>` in the pagination `<nav>`; CSS `.page-link.current { background:#1565c0; color:#fff; font-weight:700 }` gives it button affordance.\n**Fix:** Convert pagination items to `<button type=\"button\">`. This restores Space activation and is the same change that resolves the screen-reader pagination findings (SR-04, SR-05) \u2014 single fix, three symptoms.\n\n*Keyboard mechanics are otherwise sound: every control is reachable, operable, has a strong visible focus ring, and meets target size. The MEDIUM alarm reflected reasonable caution; the deep pass finds no blocking keyboard defect.*\n\n---\n\n## Perspective 6 \u2014 Screen Reader & Semantic Structure (HIGH)\n\n### JTBD checklist\n\n| Item (WCAG) | Result | Evidence |\n|---|---|---|\n| Landmarks present/correct (1.3.1) | PARTIAL | `role=\"region\" aria-label=\"Employee directory\"` and `<nav aria-label=\"Table pagination\">` exist \u2014 but the **tabular relationships** are absent (see SR-01). |\n| Heading hierarchy (2.4.6) | N/A | No headings in this fragment. |\n| Informative images have alt; decorative `alt=\"\"` (1.1.1) | PASS | Sort glyphs are text in an `aria-hidden=\"true\"` span \u2014 correctly hidden decoration. |\n| DOM order = visual order (1.3.2) | PASS | Source order matches rendered order. |\n| Unique descriptive title (2.4.2) | N/A | Document-level SC. |\n| Link purpose in context (2.4.4) | **FINDING (SR-05)** | Pagination links read only \"1\", \"2\", \"3\". |\n| `lang` on `<html>` (3.1.1) | N/A | Document-level SC. |\n| Foreign phrases wrapped (3.1.2) | N/A | Single language content. |\n| Inputs have associated labels (3.3.2) | N/A | No form inputs. |\n| Errors identify field via `aria-describedby` (3.3.1) | N/A | No error/validation UI. |\n| Custom widgets use correct APG roles (4.1.2) | **FINDING (SR-01, SR-02, SR-04)** | Div-grid \"table\"; sort buttons lack `aria-sort`; pagination lacks `aria-current`. |\n| Status messages use `aria-live` (4.1.3) | **FINDING (SR-03)** | Result count region is a plain `<div>`. |\n| SPA route change management | N/A | No client routing. |\n\n### Red-flag check\n- \"Custom widget with no ARIA role\" \u2014 **FIRES.** The sortable data grid is a custom widget rebuilt from `<div>`s with no `role=\"table\"`/`grid` and no row/columnheader/cell roles. \u2192 auto-CRITICAL (SR-01).\n\n### Findings\n\n**Finding:** The entire table is built from CSS-grid `<div>`s \u2014 no `<table>`, `<thead>`, `<tbody>`, `<tr>`, `<th scope>`, or `<td>`, and no ARIA `table`/`grid`/`row`/`columnheader`/`cell` roles. Screen-reader users get a flat stream (\"Name Department Salary Start Date \u2026 Alice Nguyen Engineering $112,000 2019-03-12 \u2026\") with **no programmatic association between a column header and the cell values beneath it**, and **no table navigation mode** (JAWS/NVDA row/column commands are unavailable). For a data table, this removes the primary way SR users consume the content.\n**WCAG:** 1.3.1 Info and Relationships (Level A)\n**Perspective:** Screen Reader & Semantic Structure\n**Severity:** CRITICAL (red flag: custom widget with no role; and a data table's core relationships are not programmatically determinable)\n**Route to:** Front-End Dev (secondary: UX Design)\n**Evidence:** `<div className=\"data-table\" role=\"region\" aria-label=\"Employee directory\">` with header/data rows composed of `<div className=\"table-cell\">`; CSS `.table-row { display:grid; grid-template-columns:2fr 1.5fr 1fr 1fr }`. No `<th>`, no `scope`, no table roles anywhere.\n**Fix:** Rebuild with native `<table>`: `<thead><tr><th scope=\"col\">` for headers (wrapping the existing sort `<button>`), `<tbody><tr><td>` for data. Native semantics restore header/cell association, row/column navigation, and count/position announcements at no ARIA cost. If the grid layout must stay, apply ARIA `role=\"table\"` + `row`/`columnheader`/`cell` \u2014 but native `<table>` is strongly preferred.\n\n**Finding:** Sort column headers expose **no `aria-sort`**. When an SR user activates a header, nothing announces that the column is now sorted or in which direction; the only direction cue (\u25b2/\u25bc) is inside an `aria-hidden=\"true\"` span. The user sorts blind and must re-read the data to infer what happened.\n**WCAG:** 4.1.2 Name, Role, Value (Level A)\n**Perspective:** Screen Reader & Semantic Structure\n**Severity:** MAJOR \u2014 state is fully hidden from AT, but the control still activates and data does reorder (not a hard block).\n**Route to:** Front-End Dev (secondary: UX Design)\n**Evidence:** `<button className={`sort-btn ${sortKey===col.key ? `sort-${sortDir}` : ''}`} onClick={() => handleSort(col.key)}>` \u2014 class toggles `sort-asc`/`sort-desc` (visual only); no `aria-sort` attribute is ever set on the header.\n**Fix:** On the header element carrying each column, set `aria-sort=\"ascending\" | \"descending\"` for the active column and `aria-sort=\"none\"` (or omit) for the rest, driven by `sortKey`/`sortDir`. Pairs with the `<th scope=\"col\">` from SR-01.\n\n**Finding:** The \"Showing X\u2013Y of Z employees\" result summary is a plain `<div>` with **no `aria-live`**. When sort or page changes, the count and the visible rows update silently \u2014 SR users receive no confirmation that anything changed.\n**WCAG:** 4.1.3 Status Messages (Level AA)\n**Perspective:** Screen Reader & Semantic Structure\n**Severity:** MAJOR\n**Route to:** Front-End Dev (secondary: UX Design)\n**Evidence:** `<div className=\"table-meta\">Showing {\u2026}\u2013{\u2026} of {sorted.length} employees</div>` \u2014 no `aria-live`, `role=\"status\"`, or `aria-atomic`.\n**Fix:** Add `role=\"status\"` (implicit `aria-live=\"polite\"`) and `aria-atomic=\"true\"` to the meta region, and include the active sort in its text (e.g., \"Showing 1\u20135 of 12 employees, sorted by Salary, descending\") so one announcement conveys count, page, and sort state after each change.\n\n**Finding:** The current page in the pagination is indicated **only visually** (`.page-link.current` background/weight). There is **no `aria-current=\"page\"`**, so an SR user cannot determine which page they are on.\n**WCAG:** 4.1.2 Name, Role, Value (Level A)\n**Perspective:** Screen Reader & Semantic Structure\n**Severity:** MAJOR\n**Route to:** Front-End Dev (secondary: UX Design)\n**Evidence:** `<a \u2026 className={`page-link ${i === page ? 'current' : ''}`}>{i + 1}</a>`; CSS `.page-link.current { background:#1565c0; color:#fff; font-weight:700 }`. No `aria-current`.\n**Fix:** Set `aria-current=\"page\"` on the active pagination control (and drop `href=\"#\"` when converting to `<button>`, per SR-05).\n\n**Finding:** Pagination items are `<a href=\"#\">` with visible/accessible text of only \"1\", \"2\", \"3\". SR users hear \"1, link\" / \"2, link\" with **no purpose** (\"Page 2 of 3\" is never conveyed), and `href=\"#\"` announces no real destination while risking a jump to the top of the document on activation. The controls perform an in-page state change, so a link is the wrong role.\n**WCAG:** 2.4.4 Link Purpose (In Context) (Level A); also 4.1.2 Name, Role, Value (Level A)\n**Perspective:** Screen Reader & Semantic Structure\n**Severity:** MAJOR\n**Route to:** Front-End Dev (secondary: Content Author)\n**Evidence:** `{Array.from({length: totalPages}, (_, i) => (<a key={i} href=\"#\" className={`page-link \u2026`} onClick={(e)=>{e.preventDefault(); setPage(i);}}>{i + 1}</a>))}` inside `<nav aria-label=\"Table pagination\">`.\n**Fix:** Use `<button type=\"button\">` for each page and give each an unambiguous accessible name \u2014 e.g. `aria-label=\"Go to page 2\"` (or visible \"Page 2\"). Combined with SR-04's `aria-current=\"page\"`, the SR user hears \"Go to page 2, button\" and \"page 3, current page, button.\" Content Author supplies the \"Page N\" wording. (This is the same element change that fixes the keyboard Space-key symptom, K-01.)\n\n---\n\n## Perspective 7 \u2014 Cognitive & Neurodivergent (MEDIUM)\n\n### JTBD checklist\n\n| Item (WCAG) | Result | Evidence |\n|---|---|---|\n| Errors suggest specific correction (3.3.3) | N/A | No forms/validation. |\n| Multi-step form no re-ask (3.3.7) | N/A | No forms. |\n| Auth allows paste/autofill, no puzzle (3.3.8) | N/A | No authentication. |\n| Nav same relative position across pages (3.2.3) | N/A | Single component; cross-page not observable. |\n| Same-function components consistent (3.2.4) | PASS | All four sort headers share one control pattern; all page controls share one pattern. |\n| Help mechanism consistent location (3.2.6) | N/A | No help mechanism. |\n| Focus does not auto-change context (3.2.1) | PASS | Sort/page act on activation, never on focus. |\n| Changing value does not auto-submit/navigate (3.2.2) | PASS | Sorting resets to page 1 (`setPage(0)`) \u2014 but this is triggered by an explicit **button activation**, not a settings-input change, and re-anchoring to page 1 after a re-sort is the conventional, expected result (page 3 of a new order would be meaningless). Not a change-of-context defect. |\n| Destructive actions have undo/confirm (3.3.4) | N/A | No destructive actions. |\n| More than one way to reach a page (2.4.5) | N/A | Site-level SC. |\n| Personal-data inputs have `autocomplete` (1.3.5) | N/A | No inputs. |\n| Timeout warnings \u226520s (2.2.1) | N/A | No timeouts. |\n| Avoids unexplained jargon / complex sentences | PASS | Labels are plain (Name, Department, Salary, Start Date). Dates render as ISO 8601 (`2019-03-12`) \u2014 unambiguous; a friendlier format would aid readability but no AA SC requires it, so this is a usability note, not a finding. |\n\n### Neurodivergent-specific checks\n\n| Item | Result | Evidence |\n|---|---|---|\n| Predictable layout, no unexpected shifts | PASS | Structure is stable across sort/page; only cell values change. |\n| Clear visual hierarchy | PASS | Header row is bold on `#f5f5f5`; rows separated by `1px` borders. |\n| No autoplay media / unprompted modals | PASS | None present. |\n| Instructions not reliant on memory | PASS | No multi-step sequence. |\n\n### Red-flag check\nCAPTCHA / paste-blocking / redundant re-entry / unconfirmed destructive action \u2014 **none fire.**\n\n### Findings\n**None (no citable AA cognitive defect).**\n\nThe MEDIUM alarm was reasonable caution, but the deep pass finds the cognitive/neurodivergent checklist clean at AA on this component. The one adjacent concern \u2014 users needing clear feedback that sort/page state changed \u2014 is genuinely a *programmatic announcement* gap already captured as SR-02/SR-03, and its remedy (a visible, explicit \"sorted by Salary, descending\" status string in the meta region) also serves neurodivergent users who may not register the small colored arrow. That fix is tracked under SR-03; manufacturing a duplicate cognitive finding without a distinct WCAG citation would be dead output, so it is noted here rather than counted.\n\n---\n\n## Contract-Compatible Evidence Blocks (new CRITICAL/MAJOR findings)\n\n### A11y Evidence Finding\nfinding_id: data-table-no-semantic-table\nfingerprint: 3f9a1c7d2e4b608a\nsource: perspective-audit Screen Reader & Semantic Structure checklist\nwcag_or_apg: WCAG 2.2 SC 1.3.1 Info and Relationships (A); WAI-ARIA APG Table / Sortable Table pattern\nsection_508_fpc_context: In scope \u2014 Revised Section 508 501/504 incorporate WCAG 2.0 A/AA; 1.3.1 is WCAG 2.0\nseverity: CRITICAL\nperspective_alarms: screen_reader_semantic=HIGH (confirmed), keyboard_motor=MEDIUM, cognitive_neurodivergent=MEDIUM\nevidence: `<div className=\"data-table\" role=\"region\">` with `<div className=\"table-cell\">` grid; CSS `.table-row { display:grid; grid-template-columns:2fr 1.5fr 1fr 1fr }`; no `<table>/<th scope>/<td>` or table/grid roles\nreproduction_steps: Source review; confirm with NVDA/JAWS \u2014 table navigation keys inactive, headers not announced with cells\nexpected_behavior: SR announces column header with each cell and offers table row/column navigation\nactual_behavior: Flat reading order; no header-to-cell association; no table mode\ntrend: new\n\n### A11y Evidence Finding\nfinding_id: data-table-missing-aria-sort\nfingerprint: 7b2e5d1f9c3a4068\nsource: perspective-audit Screen Reader & Semantic Structure checklist\nwcag_or_apg: WCAG 2.2 SC 4.1.2 Name, Role, Value (A); WAI-ARIA APG aria-sort on columnheader\nsection_508_fpc_context: In scope \u2014 4.1.2 is WCAG 2.0 A\nseverity: MAJOR\nperspective_alarms: screen_reader_semantic=HIGH, keyboard_motor=MEDIUM\nevidence: `<button className={`sort-btn ${sortKey===col.key ? `sort-${sortDir}`:''}`}>`; direction glyph in `aria-hidden=\"true\"` span; no `aria-sort`\nreproduction_steps: Source review; activate a header with SR running \u2014 no sort-state announcement\nexpected_behavior: Active column exposes aria-sort=\"ascending\"/\"descending\"; others \"none\"\nactual_behavior: No aria-sort; sort state is visual-only\ntrend: new\n\n### A11y Evidence Finding\nfinding_id: data-table-no-live-region\nfingerprint: 5c4d8e2a1f6b3097\nsource: perspective-audit Screen Reader & Semantic Structure checklist\nwcag_or_apg: WCAG 2.2 SC 4.1.3 Status Messages (AA)\nsection_508_fpc_context: Not in Revised Section 508 scope (4.1.3 is a WCAG 2.1 addition; 508 references WCAG 2.0) \u2014 still required for WCAG 2.2 AA conformance\nseverity: MAJOR\nperspective_alarms: screen_reader_semantic=HIGH, cognitive_neurodivergent=MEDIUM\nevidence: `<div className=\"table-meta\">Showing {\u2026}\u2013{\u2026} of {sorted.length} employees</div>` \u2014 no aria-live/role=\"status\"/aria-atomic\nreproduction_steps: Source review; change sort or page with SR running \u2014 no announcement\nexpected_behavior: Count/page/sort change announced politely once per update\nactual_behavior: Silent update\ntrend: new\n\n### A11y Evidence Finding\nfinding_id: data-table-no-aria-current\nfingerprint: 9a1f3c7e5b2d4860\nsource: perspective-audit Screen Reader & Semantic Structure checklist\nwcag_or_apg: WCAG 2.2 SC 4.1.2 Name, Role, Value (A); WAI-ARIA aria-current=\"page\"\nsection_508_fpc_context: In scope \u2014 4.1.2 is WCAG 2.0 A\nseverity: MAJOR\nperspective_alarms: screen_reader_semantic=HIGH\nevidence: `<a className={`page-link ${i===page ? 'current':''}`}>` with CSS `.page-link.current` styling only; no aria-current\nreproduction_steps: Source review; navigate pagination with SR \u2014 current page not identified\nexpected_behavior: Active page control exposes aria-current=\"page\"\nactual_behavior: Current page conveyed by styling only\ntrend: new\n\n### A11y Evidence Finding\nfinding_id: data-table-pagination-link-purpose\nfingerprint: 2d6b4f8a1c3e5709\nsource: perspective-audit Screen Reader & Semantic Structure checklist\nwcag_or_apg: WCAG 2.2 SC 2.4.4 Link Purpose in Context (A) + SC 4.1.2 Name, Role, Value (A)\nsection_508_fpc_context: In scope \u2014 2.4.4 and 4.1.2 are WCAG 2.0 A\nseverity: MAJOR\nperspective_alarms: screen_reader_semantic=HIGH, keyboard_motor=MEDIUM (shared root cause with K-01)\nevidence: `<a href=\"#\" onClick={(e)=>{e.preventDefault(); setPage(i);}}>{i + 1}</a>` inside `<nav aria-label=\"Table pagination\">`\nreproduction_steps: Source review; SR reads \"1, link\" with no page context; Space key scrolls instead of paging\nexpected_behavior: `<button>` per page with name \"Go to page N\" (+ aria-current on active)\nactual_behavior: Non-descriptive anchors used as buttons; href=\"#\" no destination\ntrend: new\n\n---\n\n## Perspective Audit Summary\n\n**Component/artifact reviewed:** SortableTable (React data table with sortable columns + pagination)\n**Perspectives escalated for deep review:** Keyboard & Motor Access (MEDIUM), Screen Reader & Semantic Structure (HIGH), Cognitive & Neurodivergent (MEDIUM)\n**Perspectives at LOW (not reviewed):** Magnification & Reflow, Environmental Contrast, Vestibular & Motion Sensitivity, Auditory Access\n\n### Findings by Severity\n\n| Severity | Count |\n|---|---|\n| CRITICAL | 1 |\n| MAJOR | 4 |\n| MINOR | 1 |\n| ENHANCEMENT | 0 |\n\n### Perspectives That Passed\n\n- **Cognitive & Neurodivergent** \u2014 all applicable checklist items PASS/N/A; no citable AA defect. State-change feedback need is served by the SR-03 fix.\n- **Keyboard & Motor Access** \u2014 no CRITICAL/MAJOR; mechanically sound (reachable, operable, strong focus ring, adequate target size). One MINOR (K-01).\n\n### Perspectives With Findings \u2014 Grouped by ARRM Role\n\n**Front-End Dev**\n- No semantic table structure (div grid) \u2014 Screen Reader & Semantic \u2014 CRITICAL \u2014 1.3.1 Info and Relationships\n- Missing `aria-sort` on sortable headers \u2014 Screen Reader & Semantic \u2014 MAJOR \u2014 4.1.2 Name, Role, Value\n- No `aria-live`/`role=\"status\"` on result summary \u2014 Screen Reader & Semantic \u2014 MAJOR \u2014 4.1.3 Status Messages\n- Missing `aria-current=\"page\"` on pagination \u2014 Screen Reader & Semantic \u2014 MAJOR \u2014 4.1.2 Name, Role, Value\n- Pagination anchors used as buttons, non-descriptive text, `href=\"#\"` \u2014 Screen Reader & Semantic \u2014 MAJOR \u2014 2.4.4 Link Purpose / 4.1.2 (secondary: Content Author for \"Page N\" wording)\n- Pagination Space-key does not activate (anchor-as-button) \u2014 Keyboard & Motor \u2014 MINOR \u2014 4.1.2 (shared root cause/fix with the pagination MAJOR above)\n\n**Visual Design**\n- None.\n\n**UX Design**\n- None as primary owner; secondary on all Front-End findings (sort-state/pagination interaction patterns).\n\n**Content Author**\n- Secondary: supply unambiguous pagination names (\"Page N\" / \"Go to page N\") as part of the pagination fix.\n\n### Open Questions Requiring Human Verification\n\n- None. All findings are code-level and confirmable from source (markup/CSS); no captions, transcripts, alt-text quality, or reading-level judgments were in scope for the escalated perspectives.\n\n### Recommended Next Step\n\n**BLOCK** \u2014 One CRITICAL finding (no programmatic table structure) means screen-reader users cannot associate values with columns or navigate the data. Do not ship until SR-01 is resolved. The four MAJOR findings (aria-sort, aria-live, aria-current, pagination element/purpose) must be fixed in the same pass to reach AA. Efficient remediation order: (1) rebuild as native `<table>` with `<th scope=\"col\">` [SR-01]; (2) add `aria-sort` bound to sort state [SR-02]; (3) convert pagination to `<button>` with \"Page N\" names + `aria-current=\"page\"` [SR-04, SR-05, K-01 \u2014 one change, three fixes]; (4) add `role=\"status\"`/`aria-atomic` to the meta region and fold sort state into its text [SR-03]. Re-test with a11y-test (axe-core + keyboard walkthrough + SR announcement capture) after fixes.\n",
